items.description:
LoHa of Daring Tact (umamusume). Please install extension on WebUI.

After installing extension, put LoHa file in your sd/models/lora folder and write LoRA notation in prompt to applying LoHa. <lora:loha_name:weight>

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. ğŸ‘

Recommended options

  • LoRA weight 0.7 ~ 0.8

  • Trigger words

    • Base

      • daring tact \(umamusume\)

    • Racing competition costume :

      • blue ascot, black gloves, wrist cuffs, long sleeves, halterneck shirt, white shirt, open jacket, layered skirt, collared shirt, white jacket, belt, white skirt, frills, black pantyhose

      • I think race clothes need more data.

    • Casual :

      • There is no official casual clothes of Daring Tact. So, I tried some clothes.

      • long sleeves, brown coat, open coat, yellow shirt, shirt stuck in skirt, suspenders, plaid skirt, black skirt, brown shorts

      • turtleneck sweater, black sweater, ribbed sweater, long sleeves, bracelet, denim pants, belt

    • Tracen summer uniform :

      • tracen school uniform, summer uniform, serafuku, puffy short sleeves, purple bowtie, horseshoe ornament, sailor collar, sailor shirt, purple shirt, white skirt, pleated skirt, frills, miniskirt, zettai ryouiki, white thighhighs, brown footwear, loafers

    • Tracen winter uniform :

      • tracen school uniform, winter uniform, puffy long sleeves, sailor collar, purple shirt, white bowtie, horseshoe ornament, purple skirt, pleated skirt, brown footwear, loafers

Use a model derived from or mixed with animefull model.

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • I recommend kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use Hires.fix to get higher quality image

      • Upscaler

        • Latent, Latent (nearest-exact), Latent (bicubic antialiased) or other Latent series.

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss.

    • LyCORIS by KohakuBlueleaf

    • Thank you all a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned model

  • 55 images consist of

    • 4x low quality 19 images

    • 8x medium quality 17 images

    • 16x high quality 19 images

    • => 1 epoch = 516 images

  • replaced character feature tags with daring tact \(umamusume\)

    • 1girl, green eyes, tail, long hair, aqua eyes, hair ornament, horse tail, multicolored hair, animal ears, medium hair, horse girl, black hair, hair between eyes, streaked hair, ahoge, simple background, solo, blue eyes, horse ears, brown hair, star hair ornament

    • I think these tags are the essentials of daring tact.

    • or unnecessary for training because of duplication.

  • resolution : 768x768 with aspect ratio bucketing.

  • other training settings is included in training_data.zip or metadata in LoRA file.

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

And, special thanks to my best friend. DH.

items.name: sanpaku eyes
items.description:
This LORA model is trained on an image of a sanpaku eyes (small iris).

V1.0

The iris becomes smaller when the weight is increased. However, if the weight is raised too high, the image becomes rough. 1.2 or lower is better.

The image of a boy has a smaller iris than that of a girl.

Angry, surprised, wide-eyed prompts work better.

For realistic checkpoints, an older, more realistic person is generated.

V2.0

In version 2, the training step was increased to generate more smaller iris while using the same input images.

LoRA weights can now be used with a weight of 1.

When adapted to realistic models, it produces younger person than version 1(why?).

items.description:
Hurt her friends and she will break your kneecaps!

General Info

This LoRA has been made to create pictures of Kurugaya Yuiko, who is my favourite character of the hearwarming and emotional series called Little Busters! The model allows for you to display in most of her outfits annd allows for a few interesting poses. The compatibility with semi-realistic models can be quite impressive and let you display her in artstyles that differ from the classic style of the anime or visual novel.

Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. It is very important to use the relevant trigger word so that you can get results that look close to mine or even better. I advise using a weight of 0.6-0.8 but you might even be able to go lower in some cases.

items.description:
Courteney Cox is an American actress known for the sitcom Friends and the film franchise Scream, amongst many other roles.

My goal with this TI was to capture her looks in the late 80s and early 90s.

I trained the TI for 1000 steps, but it got overtrained pretty soon and I ended up setting for step 400, which might still be very slightly overtrained too, but looks really accurate in my opinion. In any case, I recommend using the embedding at a reduced weight. For instance, type "(c0urt400:0.99)" in your prompt. That should solve any issue in most cases.

How to use this LoRA model? (AUTOMATIC1111)

  1. Drop the LoRA into the "stable-diffusion-webui/models/Lora" folder and start AUTOMATIC1111.

  2. Write your prompt as usual in e.g. text2img or img2img but also include "with pokies" when describing the clothing.

  4. A new section under the prompt will appear, go to the Lora tab there and select this model

items.name: Fantasy Character Style - RPG heroes concept art [fantasyheroes]
items.description:
What is this?

Style of heroic fantasy animal-human mixes. Trained with a dataset of 68 character concept art images.

How to use

Save to your embeddings folder in SD installation. Prompt the file with fantasycharacter

Recommended settings

CFG Scale: I tested all images with 7, feel free to experiment with lower values, from 4 to 5.5 to give it more freedom.

Steps: 30 will produce concept art, 50 solid digital artwork, 100-150 for highly detailed renders.

Positive prompt

Formula:

[Medium] of [Subject constants], [Subject Descriptions], [Style tags], [Beautifier tags], [Model Specific Tags]

See a complete list of positive prompts you can use in the version description here, just add your desired medium in front.

Negative prompt:

Because of a few training images, it is recommended to add these:

watermark, logo, artist name, signature, text

The example I used is a mix of a few negative embeddings plus some words I added myself to fine-tune the results:

ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, bad-artist, bad-hands-5, lowres, ((bad anatomy)), blurry, ((mutated hands and fingers)), (poorly drawn face), ((mutation)), ((deformed face)), (ugly), ((bad proportions)), ((extra limbs)), extra face, (double head), (extra head), ((extra feet)), logo, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg, humpbacked, long body, long neck, ((jpeg artifacts)), (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, normal quality, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale)), artist name, watermark, logo, signature, text, out of the image, out of frame, pale colors, NSWF, nude

Canvas size

512x768 with a highres fix at 1.5 times and Denosing at 0.5

Model recommendations

I tested this on 10+ models (see examples) and concluded this:

  1. Anime models will do humans with cat ears. Tested 3-4, maybe you get lucky.

  2. Standard quality results with general purpose models like Deliberate and Midjourney family, DreamShaper and Dreamlike Diffusion.

  3. Interesting results with specialized models like RPGv4 (killing on the outfit side), should be interesting with "furry" models (for example FurryMix) or PixarStyle for Disney-like characters.

  4. Amazing results with WestMagic. I expect Asian graphics models to kill the outfit and standing pose.

All the models you can find in the Civitai search.

Beyond the Examples

Feel free to experiment with other models, style strengths (other than 1.0), low CFG (3-5.5) and high steps (100-150) combinations on high-performing models, or anything else that crossed your mind.

Make sure to share the results in the comments.

Follow us for more

Peaksel team is inspired by the willingness of this community to share and is grateful for all the tools and knowledge we got here. This is why we plan to share all the best tools we make. Follow us to stay in the loop.

items.name: AniShaded - Style
items.description:
Did you know that not all my LoRAs are hosted on CivitAI? Check out my Patreon to learn more!

What's this LoRA

This is a LoRA trained on a particular style. It creates images with a reduced color palette and shading.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my custom: https://civitai.com/models/24149)

You don't need to specify a word to trigger this LoRA.

The LoRA works very well also on NSFW (check last examples).

Training Images

All the images on which this LoRA was trained were also generated using Stable Diffusion.

Here's a sample (v1):

V2 was trained on the example pictures you see here on CivitAI.

V1 or V2

  • V1 is trained on pictures generated with different SD models and has a darker tone

  • V2 is trained on pictures generated with my models, so it works better on anime portraits. It also has brighter colors.

Tips for this LoRA

  • For the pictures in the examples, I've used a weight of 0.5, but you can use a higher value without any problems.

  • This LoRA works wonderful with close-ups and portraits.

  • This LoRA works very well with my Sapphire and Anime models. It has also a nice effect on my Ruby model (but it is harder to use at high weights).

  • It is biased towards moles on the character face, so be sure to add that to the negative prompt if you do not want them.

items.name: Realistic Socks - Sexy Legs and Feet (NSFW)
items.description:
Let's celebrate beautiful socks!

Download this model and activate it with a strength of 0.3-0.7 (I use 0.6). No arbitrary keywords needed, but make sure you mention socks otherwise the feet might be cut off in the image.

This LoRa is great for adding socks to a variety of poses. HOWEVER, it's not the greatest at handling soles. I made a LoRa specifically for that purpose, here: https://civitai.com/models/26357/realistic-socks-soles-sexy-legs-and-feet-nsfw

Usage:

Avoid the word "feet" since it skews the AI towards rendering toes, which often ruin the soft sock details.

Example Prompts + Notes:

General Purpose: "Woman wearing socks, legs spread"

Very high quality, but often just feet: "legs, pink socks"

Use the "legs spread" pose for fairly strong results: "legs spread, blue striped socks"

Try your own pose descriptions, but make sure you mention 'socks' in the prompt - it helps to emphasize with (): "(yellow socks), woman, sexy, [[Your chosen pose]]"

You can also leave a trail of destruction as she walks though a city.

I've found this lora works best if you use a inpainting checkpoint and set the Inpainting conditioning mask strength to something less than 1, but your mileage may vary.

items.name: [WIP] Thick Tail | Feature

I have been working to integrate various unique features into LoRa's (and now LyCORIS). I have found making individual trainings on each feature, then merging the ones needed together gets remarkable results.

This has been trained on about 50 AI generated images from various models (picked out from hundreds), after using android 21 as a reference.

This can be used stand-alone to add a thick skin like tail, or mixed with other LoRA / LyCORIS to mix the feature in. I recommend to avoid using this with multiple other LoRA / LyCORIS without mixing first, it is more prone to cause issues.

items.name: Graphic Novel - Style
items.description:
IMPORTANT NOTICE:

Hello everyone! Lately in the comments I have often seen people complaining that my LoRA are similar to each other or are not representative of the style they should represent. My models are not trained on material from other artists, and it is therefore difficult to explain what the actual output should be. Since preparing the material necessary for the publication of a LoRA usually takes me a day's work, I have therefore decided not to post all my LoRAs on CivitAI anymore, but from today I will only post those that I consider interesting enough for the audience of this site. If you are interested in downloading the other LoRA as well, you will find them all for FREE (and they'll always be) on my Patreon page (subscribers will have early access to each of these). Thank you all for your support!

I've started a community on Deviant Art to share images made with my models/LoRAs! Join here if you are interested!

IF YOU ARE NEW TO STABLE DIFFUSION OR YOU HAVE PROBLEMS WITH MY MODELS GO HERE: Guide

What's this LoRA

This is a LoRA trained on a particular style. It creates images with the style of a sci-fi graphic Novel.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my custom: https://civitai.com/models/24149)

You don't need to specify a word to trigger this LoRA.

The LoRA works also on NSFW (check last examples).

You can check how it works on Anime with a lower weight in the second half of the examples.

Flavors

The LoRA is available in 2 different flavors:

  • Standard: The original one. This is biased towards a particular color scheme.

  • Bright: This one is mixed with other two LoRAs (twisted and whale) and has a wider color palette

items.name: Retro Spaceships
items.description:
This Lora was trained on images of 70's retro-futurist style spaceships. It seems to hold the style well, but the spaceships it makes are often nonsensical in design; with little to no symmetry. Getting a good result may take more than a few tries. It may do better with things like controlnet, but I haven't tried it yet.

Recommend strength around 0.7, CFG will vary on model.

I've attempted to get it trained on specific styles of design. These aren't strictly necessary to produce results so long as paired with some other prompts, but may nudge the ships toward a certain design aesthetic:

'Spherical Design' - As the name implies, intended to create spherical spaceships.

'Ring Design' - Barely functional.

'Organic Design' - Intended for ships with rounded shapes to it

'Sleek Design' - Intended for more classic aerodynamic designs that are less bulky; but in my preliminary experiments seems to overlap with the organic design prompt a lot of the time; effect may be more noticeable when using the same seed but different design prompts.

'Box Design' - Meant to create more angular and bulkier designs, but needs to be paired with the 'Sharp Angles' prompt for full effect.

'Insectoid Design' - As the name implies. Creates ships substantially different from the other design prompts.

Additional prompts: 'Wings', 'Sharp Angles', 'Antenna', 'engine exhaust', 'Flying over landscape', 'Flying over lunar landscape', 'Flying over city', 'Nebula', 'Asteroids', 'Cockpit Exterior', 'Detailed Hull' 'color hull', 'legs', 'landed'

items.name: Azazel Ameri - Iruma-kun
items.description:
Updating this to V2 with the biggest change coming around increasing the Lora's ability to be used with other Lora/Locon's, as well as being used in other models. Added images to show these improvements. Also, it was trained on animefull_final now instead of AnythingV3.

Picture Descriptions:

1-2: AnythingV3 using just this Lora.

3: AnythingV3 with the Lora and "wearing a business suit" prompt

4: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Pet Play Locon

5: AnythingV3 combo'd with my released Brainwashing Locon.

6: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Symbiote Taking Over Locon.

7: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress V2Corruption Locon.

8: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Dominatrix Locon and my in progress being Stepped On Locon.

9: MeinaPastel with just this Lora.

10: AbyssOrange with just this Lora.

11: PerfectWorld using just this Lora.

---------------------------------v1 info below and still relevant-----------------------------------

One more, more standard, LORA for today! This one is based off another lesser seen character who I love. Specifically, Azazel Ameri, from Iruma-kun. It was trained on AnythingV3 with 56 images. Unsure if I'll have a second version come out for this one, as I think it works well. Let me know for any specific things you may want.

What does it do you ask? Pretty simple for this one. You put in the LORA, you get back everyone's (well, mine at least) favorite romance manga loving demon girl. Using simple prompts so that you can see it's relatively easy to get a good picture out of this.

How to use it: Trigger word is AmeriA. I prefer the LORA strength being ~0.7. I also recommend adding:

AmeriCL, wearing AmeriCL- To push her own outfit more.
pink thighhighs, orange high heel boots - These are the main features that are not hyper consistant (the colors blend too much at times), so reminding it will increase consistency.

Extra, Extra!: Seems relatively easy to change clothes for her (added a swimsuit one for that purpose). After that were two pictures that I used ControlNet + OpenPose to make, so the prompt won't work if you just copy paste it sadly. Finally, the last picture shows combining it with another LORA for clothing -> gothGalArmored_v10. It's an awesome clothing LORA, go grab it yourself!


What's next for this? Unsure if I'll have a second version come out for this one, as I think it works well. Let me know for any specific things you may want.

What's next that isn't this? Same as my previous upload because it hasn't been a day yet >.<. Probably plan to release a couple more character Loras from Anime (Maki from Fire Force, Miku + Piscalat from Idaten Deities, Makoto from P5, and Sae + Shadow Sae from P5.) Maybe some other more general ones like my corruption LORA (thinking about a brainwashing one). I may also try out Locon's as I've seen they do an even better job than Lora's. Or just give me some random suggestion. That works too.

Trained using the LyCORIS method implemented by KohakuBlueleaf, the method to use this model should already be available in the model type instruction that this site provides.

Compatibility

Trained on NAI, making it compatible with any anime model mixes that aren't based off waifudiffusion.

Recommended Weight

A great LORA/LOHA/LOCON will always work with 1.0 without being fried, the only time when I recommend you lower this to 0.7-0.8 is when you plan on mixing this model with other models.

Trigger Tokens/Additional Activation Tokens

"nurseperseus" will be the trigger token for this character, you can use additional tokens like

"black choker, center opening, cleavage, half gloves, id card, nurse, nurse cap, pink eyes, pink gloves, pink hair, twintails, very long hair, white headwear, white thighhighs, pink heels, jacket"

you may also want to put one of these tags into the negative prompt box if you plan on changing her outfit completely, it is possible however you may need to put one of her main tags into the negative prompt box while doing some variation seeds.

"Glasses, red eyewear, semi-rim glasses"

will help you get the glasses she wears as well with this outfit

items.name: Reinbolt (+ Mini LORA tutorial)
items.description:
Hi, this is my first post here.

My name is david and I'm a professional concept/3D artist who currently is doing AI workflows (currently in Substance Designer and Photoshop mostly). I started using AI in my works around 6 months ago when discovered Disco Diffusion and later MidJourney till I stall with Stable Diffusion. Since then I have been daily finetunning and training models for me and other people (mostly AI instagram artists) and recently I opened a patreon (with 2 other fellas) so people could support us in the model finetunning/making and experiments/workflows. If you think what we are doing is good, feel free to support us. Thanks!

Also if you want to check my works or just my daily basis feel free to check my IG at @davidsayszawarudoagain

--

This is the result of the mini tutorial I have put on our patreon for free.
https://www.patreon.com/posts/workflow-how-to-80636187

EDIT: Settings since probably someone want to test them or just know how was trained:

200 repeats per image, 30-40 images, epoch 6-8, lrate/urate default in this case, ClipSkip 2, max vector token 1, FP16 in both areas, constant without warm ups and trained over a custom model in DIM/NET 8x8 . Nothing to hide here. Input is more important than this "magical settings".

A bit different of what people use to do when training but I think it's lot of fun. Feel free to test a bit this char and tell me if works or not. As a quick difference this wasn't trained on SD 1.5 or NAI/Anything/Abyss, rather than that I used a custom finetunned model that did a decent job.

Lora weight works even at higher than 1 but recommended is 0.7-1. 0-5-0.6 should give you some char design style. Keyword is "reinbolt" and if somehow you can't see his green armor with lightings put "green" or "armor", it should appear.

By the way, as everything from my part, feel free to sell, transform, mix or whatever you want. Just have fun and throw some feedback if possible.

items.description:
Hello everyone! My third and no where near final model. Today I have two new ones, another one I'll be uploading in a bit but this one first for now. First off, thanks for the support on the last model. But enough shameless thanks. Lets get on to da good stuff!

First off, this is yet another mix going for a semi realistic look. But this one is better. It is very good with faces, I'm gonna get that off to you right now. It is extremely good as well with details and all that fluff. However, the colors are VERY flat on this one, if you want just add: (saturated, popping colors:0.7) to lighten up the photo a bit. Its ok with NSFW. Unlike my last mix. Anyways I mixed it with a custom mix, but basically the gist is:

  • AOMA3 (25%), AmborsiaFusion (25%), and Counterfiet2.5 (50% for that realistic goodness.

Below is the recommended settings for BMM.

  • CFG Scale 10.

  • Steps Test: 20. Illustration: 30.

  • Upscaler Latent Your pick

  • Sampler DPM +++ SDE Karras

  • Prompts: Can be semi advanced, the CFG scale factors this a lot.

  • Negative prompts: Simple is best, here is the recommended negative prompt: "(worst quality, low quality:1.4), EasyNegative, bad_prompt_version2, disfigured, shallow eyes, fractured eyes."

Anyways. below is photos using all of these steps right here above. Just to show how good this model is. (Steps in the photos.) If it randomly generates nsfw, put nsfw first in the negative prompts if going for a SFW image. All images shown below are also from the first image I got with using this prompt, no minute long redoing, just straight to the point. (No inpainting as well,)

items.name: Ava Max
items.description:
A likeness of the singer Ava Max. This is the first attempt and I hope to refine it. It can be hit or miss at times, but I wanted to focus at first on the unique hair.

v1.4: Started from scratch. I have a bit more experience now and was hoping that would show in the results. This is still a fussy model. I had better luck with ver 1.5 as the model than realistic vision v3. The 2 hair lengths go against what pretty much all other known data has and I think it is making this resist that. Probably will release 1.5 with more images so the model 'sees' her hair like that more (or more epocs).

v1.1 , still finicky. Weights should be kept low. Sometimes it renders her iconic hairstyle. I found (thin lips) added to the prompt helped out. Definitely need to overhaul the dataset.

modelVersions.description: complete restart from scratch

items.name: Large Futanari LoRA
items.description:
This is my Futanari LoRA, focused on larger and more pronounced phallic imagery. It has a harder time doing flaccid and non-erect imagery.

As usual, the strength is good from 0.6 to 0.8, but I use 0.75.

Though this LoRA heavily assists with making futanari imagery, if your model can't handle penis generation well, it can only help so much. Granted that most models can only do penis generation coherently around 50%-70% of the time, expect better but similar results.

Beware that I accidentally left in "large testicles" in the training dataset tags, and applying this to your prompt makes it likely that you'll generate a woman with only testicles. This can possibly happen without this tag, but I've only gotten one generation like so.

The keywords are 'zfuta' and 'futanari'. These two in conjunction can produce good results, and often you do not need many more tags in order to get a good result.

All pictures were generated with my custom blends, available on my profile. I used the Orangemix VAE with Hires Fix on. I trained this LoRA with NAI and used 300 images for the dataset.

items.name: MH Zinogre Themer
items.description:
Excels at creating Anthro Zinogre, Monster Girl Zinogre and Zinogre People in general ->

For Anthros and Monster Girls, my best results came from using Dreamshaper, LawlassYiffyMix20 or Dungeons and Waifus as the base model. Include these in your prompt: (zinogre:0.5) <lora:zinogre:0.5>

Other notable models I tried: Kenshi, Deliberate and Counterfeit.

MY BEST RESULTS CAME FROM MAKING THE STRENGTH OF BOTH THE LoRA TAG AND THE "Zinogre" TRIGGER WORD 0.5 OR LESS THAN 0.5.
ANY STRENGTHS ABOVE 0.5 ARE ALMOST GUARANTEED TO PRODUCE A ZINOGRE FACE SOMEWHERE IN YOUR PICTURE. YOU CAN ALSO INCLUDE "Zinogre" IN YOUR NEGATIVE PROMPT TO IMPROVE CHANCES OF GETTING ZINOGRE THEMING WITHOUT HIS CUTE DOGGY FACE IN THE PICTURE!

I am still actively fine-tuning this model to make it even more versatile than I've already found it to be.


This model will attempt to create Zinogre from Monster Hunter or will turn people into variants of Zinogre themed people or anthros.

Trained on SD1.5 using images from both MHW and MH:Rise.
